Per a recently approved cross-project spec, new migrations shouldn't have a dowgrade path. Why was one added here?

Patch Set 4:

Ian, it's not an easy question and in other projects it's discussed to abandon downgrades. Since we don't have this dissension in Glance it's better to support downgrades for now.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1 -Workflow

Still strongly -1 on the inclusion of the downgrade but I'll bring this up at the next meeting. (Spec for reference http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/openstack-specs/specs/no-downward-sql-migration.html)
